<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="LootActions" i="action" m="interactions.utils.loot" n="loot_WorldEp21_OnLotNotes" s="490669">
  <L n="loot_actions">
    <V t="notification_and_dialog">
      <U n="notification_and_dialog">
        <V n="dialog" t="notification">
          <U n="notification">
            <V n="icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="resource_key">
                <U n="resource_key">
                  <T n="key" p="InGame\UI\Icons\Notifications\notification_notepad.png">2f7d0004:00000000:db4d8edeeb85566e</T>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x32E3145<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 3:</b>\nDambele earned its fame as a hub for the arts following the efforts of the Darongs. Despite all that, it seems like Adekoya and the young Darong child are not as artistically inclined...Obi was it? Yes of course...why do I remember hearing of a third child then?"--></T>
                  <T>0xECB7500C<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 2:</b>\nPlenty of rumors about the recent arrival of a foreign Noble to Dambele. Seems to have picked the Duchess' attention. Wonder what their intentions are...and how old Adekoya will handle it."--></T>
                  <T>0x923E78B1<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 1:</b>\nI've gotten several reports of people hearing strange sounds at night from the Secret Passageways in the palace. Wonder if there's a burglar using those tunnels...or perhaps it's something even saucier!"--></T>
                  <T>0xBE3CCB42<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 6:</b>\nThere's been a lot of speculation around the circumstances of Rodrigo de Pablo's death. However, I believe the evidence I've gathered proves the notorious pirate almost certainly died during a fire inside the Eppsilon submersible."--></T>
                  <T>0x98986905<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 9:</b>\nI have come to learn there are several unpublished memoirs of Princess Cordelia. They can still be found in Ondarion. I wonder if they have any information I might have missed in my previous investigations."--></T>
                  <T>0x1603FA83<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 7:</b>\nIt is well known that the pirate John Wilson was extraordinarily fond of rice. He could cook it in any shape. According to recent findings he had personal secret recipe involving a <i>very</i> big pan. There's even evidence of him using said pan to scare off his enemies."--></T>
                  <T>0x783BF35E<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 5:</b>\nThe pirates of Verdemar have been demonstrably so fond of lemons, that they caused repeated shortages of the yellow fruit throughout the history of the neighborhood. To this day, lemons are a valued and almost sacred food in Verdemar."--></T>
                  <T>0x814F0003<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 4:</b>\nIt is known that Verdemar Nobility has a long and intertwined history with pirates. Thus Cordelia Thebe V appears to have made an uncommon choice by picking an exemplary, high-ranking Noble for a husband...but has she truly settled for him?"--></T>
                  <T>0x861B51A0<!--String: "<b>The Whisperer's Journal - Note 8:</b>\nThere's been reports of vandalous acts against <i>Cuore Sepolto</i>, the statue dedicated to the history of Bellacorde and its proud Capp family. What's more intriguing however are the rumors that a member of the Capps themselves might be responsible. Could it be true?"--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
          </U>
        </V>
      </U>
    </V>
  </L>
</I>